# Analyst Kit — API keys & secrets
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `analyst-kit install` / `analyst-kit env` will prompt for any
# missing key when run interactively and write it here (the file is git-ignored).
# Skills read these from the process environment at run time.
#
# On the Claude Code / Cowork plugin you don't edit this file by hand: set the keys in
# the plugin config field (FMP_API_KEY required, FINMIND_TOKEN / SERPAPI_API_KEY
# optional) and the SessionStart hook bridges them here automatically.

# FinMind — Taiwan market data (finmind)
# Free token: register at https://finmindtrade.com/
FINMIND_TOKEN=

# Financial Modeling Prep — global fundamentals (financialmodellingprep, company-wiki)
# Key: https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/developer/docs
# On Claude Code / Cowork this is set via the plugin config field (keychain) and
# bridged here automatically by the SessionStart hook — you don't edit it by hand.
FMP_API_KEY=

# SerpAPI — Google Trends search-interest data (market-intelligence)
# Free key: https://serpapi.com/  (free tier = 100 searches/month)
SERPAPI_API_KEY=

# Note: sec-filings / 13f-analysis pull SEC EDGAR with no API key. SEC_EDGAR_UA
# (the fair-access contact string) is AUTO-GENERATED per install from a one-time
# user id, so no value is required here. Set one only to override the generated UA.
